<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFCAFFE1FF6BFE3BFD6BFC84" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFCAFFE1FF6BFE3BFD6BFC84" blockId="16.[151,1127,477,852]" pageId="16" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCAFFE1FF6BFE3BFEBBFE44" bold="true" box="[151,261,477,500]" pageId="16" pageNumber="291">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCAFFE1FEF5FE3BFE63FE44" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1921" box="[265,477,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exornata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCAFFE1FEF5FE3BFE63FE44" box="[265,477,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="291">Charidotis exornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described explicitly from a single specimen (
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCAFFE1FC20FE3BFBE5FE44" author="WEISE" box="[988,1115,477,500]" firstAuthor="WEISE" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" pagination="1 - 205" refId="ref52379" refString="WEISE J. 1921: Wissenschaftliche Ergebnise der Swedischen Entomologischen Reisen des Herrn Dr. A. Roman in Amazonas und Bahia 1914 - 15 und 1923 - 24. 6. Chrysomelidae. Arkiv for Zoologi 14 (1): 1 - 205." type="journal article" year="1921">WEISE 1921</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCAFFE1FF6BFE1BFE8BFDA4" author="SPAETH" box="[151,309,509,532]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" pagination="183 - 187" refId="ref51295" refString="SPAETH F. 1931 b: Wissenschaftliche Ergebnise der Swedischen Entomologischen Reisen des Herrn Dr. A. Roman in Amazonas und Bahia 1914 - 15 und 1923 - 24. Cassidinae. Entomologisk Tidskrift 53: 183 - 187." type="journal article" year="1931" yearSuffix="b">SPAETH (1931b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCAFFE1FEBDFE1BFEC6FDA4" author="SPAETH" box="[321,376,509,532]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" pagination="66 - 99" refId="ref51359" refString="SPAETH F. 1936: Bestimmungstabelle der Gattung Charidotis (Col. Chrys. Cassid.). Sbornik Entomologickeho Oddeleni Narodniho Musea v Praze 14: 66 - 99." type="journal article" year="1936">1936</bibRefCitation>
) considered it as an aberrant specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCAFFE1FCC6FE1BFBDDFDA4" authority="Boheman, 1855" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[826,1123,509,532]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cognata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCAFFE1FCC6FE1BFC0EFDA4" box="[826,944,509,532]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="291">C. cognata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCAFFE1FC4BFE1BFBDDFDA4" author="Boheman" box="[951,1123,509,532]" firstAuthor="Boheman" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">Boheman, 1855</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on the labels Spaeth cited, it is unclear why he considered it as a peculiar form of the latter species, as it is very different in size and morphological features. 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCAFFE1FC73FDDBFBD9FDE4" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1921" box="[911,1127,573,596]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exornata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCAFFE1FC73FDDBFBD9FDE4" box="[911,1127,573,596]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="291">Charidotis exornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct by the very broadly elliptical pronotum presented only in certain species, i.e. theses 
<quantity id="282ED3D3FFCAFFE1FF6BFD9BFEB1FD24" box="[151,271,637,660]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6929" metricValueMax="6.756399999999999" metricValueMin="6.6294" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" unit="in" value="263.5" valueMax="266.0" valueMin="261.0">261–266 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCAFFE1FEEFFD9BFE15FD24" author="SPAETH" box="[275,427,637,660]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" pagination="66 - 99" refId="ref51359" refString="SPAETH F. 1936: Bestimmungstabelle der Gattung Charidotis (Col. Chrys. Cassid.). Sbornik Entomologickeho Oddeleni Narodniho Musea v Praze 14: 66 - 99." type="journal article" year="1936">SPAETH (1936)</bibRefCitation>
, while 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCAFFE1FE09FD9BFDD6FD24" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[501,616,637,660]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cognata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCAFFE1FE09FD9BFDD6FD24" box="[501,616,637,660]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="291">C. cognata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a narrower pronotum and coarser punctation of elytra. In my opinion 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCAFFE1FE68FD7BFDAEFD04" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1921" box="[404,528,669,692]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exornata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCAFFE1FE68FD7BFDAEFD04" box="[404,528,669,692]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="291">C. exornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCAFFE1FD21FD7BFBA8FD04" authority="Boheman, 1862" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[733,1046,669,692]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circulifera">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCAFFE1FD21FD7BFCD5FD04" box="[733,875,669,692]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="291">C. circulifera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCAFFE1FC93FD7BFBA8FD04" author="Boheman" box="[879,1046,669,692]" firstAuthor="Boheman" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" refId="ref48022" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1862: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Quartus. (Supplementum). Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, vi + 504 pp." type="book" year="1862">Boheman, 1862</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as both taxa are morphologically similar, differing only in colouration. The latter has a dorsum with two concentric rings, black and red, and a yellow central spot, while in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCAFFE1FC6BFD3BFBA8FD44" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1921" box="[919,1046,733,756]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exornata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCAFFE1FC6BFD3BFBA8FD44" box="[919,1046,733,756]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="291">C. exornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the red inner ring is expanded and forms a large central spot without a yellow marking. For these reasons I synonymize 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCAFFE1FE79FCFBFDBDFC84" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1921" box="[389,515,797,820]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exornata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCAFFE1FE79FCFBFDBDFC84" box="[389,515,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="291">C. exornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCAFFE1FDBCFCFBFD71FC84" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[576,719,797,820]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circulifera">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCAFFE1FDBCFCFBFD71FC84" box="[576,719,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="291">C. circulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFCAFFE1FF6BFCDBFC89FCE4" box="[151,823,829,852]" pageId="16" pageNumber="291" type="distribution">
